  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is there any app like Shazam to get the chord tabs when hearing a song?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several apps and tools that can help you identify chords when listening to a song, similar to how Shazam works for identifying songs. Here are a few popular options:\n\n### 1. **Chordify**\n   - **How it works**: Chordify analyzes the chords of any song you upload or link to (from YouTube, Spotify, etc.) and displays the chord progression in real-time.\n   - **Platforms**: Web, iOS, Android.\n   - **Features**: Syncs chords with the song, offers transposition, and allows you to save and share chord charts.\n\n### 2. **Moises**\n   - **How it works**: Moises uses AI to separate audio tracks (e.g., vocals, drums, bass, etc.) and can identify chords for songs you upload.\n   - **Platforms**: Web, iOS, Android.\n   - **Features**: Chord detection, tempo and key adjustments, and track isolation.\n\n### 3. **Autochords**\n   - **How it works**: Autochords allows you to upload audio files or YouTube links to automatically detect and display chords.\n   - **Platforms**: Web.\n   - **Features**: Chord detection, chord progression suggestions, and MIDI file downloads.\n\n### 4. **TabFinder**\n   - **How it works**: TabFinder is a community-driven app where users can find and share guitar tabs, including chord progressions.\n   - **Platforms**: iOS, Android.\n   - **Features**: Chord and tab search, playback speed adjustment, and user-generated content.\n\n### 5. **Tunebat**\n   - **How it works**: Tunebat provides information about the key, BPM, and chord progression of songs from Spotify, Apple Music, or other sources.\n   - **Platforms**: Web.\n   - **Features**: Key and BPM detection, chord progression analysis.\n\n### 6. **Cifra Club**\n   - **How it works**: Cifra Club is a Brazilian app that offers chord tabs for a wide range of songs. It also has a chord detector feature.\n   - **Platforms**: Web, iOS, Android.\n   - **Features**: Chord detector, song chord library, and community contributions.\n\n### 7. **Soundslice**\n   - **How it works**: Soundslice syncs sheet music or tabs with video or audio, allowing you to see chords and play along.\n   - **Platforms**: Web.\n   - **Features**: Sync chord tabs with audio/video, interactive playback.\n\n### 8. **Snapchat (via Chord Detector Lens)**\n   - **How it works**: Snapchat has a Lens that can detect chords when you play a song near your phone.\n   - **Platforms**: iOS, Android.\n   - **Features**: Real-time chord detection, fun and interactive.\n\nThese apps use various techniques, including AI, machine learning, and user-generated content, to help you identify chords in songs. While they may not always be 100% accurate, they are great tools for learning and practicing music!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
